descript.abstract: Assessor's parcel data for Town of West Bridgewater. Developed from existing digital data. Geometry and attribute data updated in July 2015 reflecting the Assessor's FY16 CAMA records.

idinfo.accconst: This digital parcel data layer is considered to be in the public domain and will become accessible for download and display from the MassGIS website: http://www.mass.gov/mgis
idinfo.useconst: This data may be appropriate for planning purposes. It should not be utilized where legal and surveyed property boundaries are required.
idinfo.native: This parcel data is submitted to MassGIS in a file geodatabase. It will be incorporated into the MassGIS SDE database, and may be converted into other GIS data types for future distribution.

citeinfo.origin: Town of West Bridgewater Assessor's Office

dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

srcinfo.srccontr: The Assessor's tax maps were converted to digital format (CADD) by Sewall several years ago. Tighe & Bond converted the CADD files into a seamless parcel layer in 2007. All maps were 1"=200'.

procstep.procdesc: The Town's existing data was aligned to MassGIS 2008 orthophotography and MassGIS open space data. The data was linked to an extract from the Assessor's Patriot CAMA system. in 2014 the data was updated to include tax map updates and CAMA updates from the previous three years. The data was updated in 2015 to reflect the Assessor's FY16 data.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of West Bridgewater, Massachusetts. Edits to a base parcel file were made to the spatial and tabular data in order to bring the file in compliance with November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. These edits included ensuring that the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer and compared against the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M322Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable. Annual parcel updates completed December 2021. Geometry and attribute data updated on 11/2024
